{
  "texts": [
    "If so, it would be necessary to train on the nucleotide sequence space (61 7 for NNN, 31 7 for NNK), which is much larger than the amino acid sequence space (20 7).",
    "We observed a high correlation between the production fitness scores of the codon replicates in the modeling library (Fig. 2a and Supplementary Fig.",
    "2), suggesting no significant codon usage bias.",
    "Therefore, we averaged production fitness across codon replicates for all downstream modeling.",
    "The production fitness distribution of the modeling library could be modeled by a mixture of two Gaussian distributions: a \"non-fit\" versus a \"production-fit\" distribution (Fig. 2b)."
  ]
}